  "texts": [
    "Next, employing this optimal configuration, we analyze the performance across different language models, comparing BERT (Devlin et al., 2018), SPECTER 2.0 (Cohan et al., 2020; Singh et al., 2022), and SciBERT (Beltagy et al., 2019).",
    "These three are state-of-the-art models in natural language processing.",
    "BERT (Devlin et al., 2018) is a general-purpose language model pre-trained on a large corpus of diverse text, making it suitable for a wide range of tasks.",
    "While its broad focus might limit performance in specialized domains, it could also mitigate overfitting by capturing general language patterns, thus making it more robust when applied to various types of data.",
    "SPECTER 2.0 (Cohan et al., 2020; Singh et al., 2022) is designed specifically for scientific document embeddings, optimizing performance for citation-based tasks."
